description: For sale: $725,000. Your own slice of heaven! Get comfy in this stunning, modern farmhouse that sits on 9 acres in the Proctor School District. This custom home built in 2015 and finished in 2020 includes the most unique attention to detail. When entering your home you'll be greeted in your one of a kind silo with amazing penny flooring as a unique focal point.  Also enjoy an expansive great room that boasts a wall to wall window haven that floods the home with a ton of natural light. As you walk through your three story great room you'll find your custom kitchen that exudes the modern farmhouse feel.  The kitchen includes quality crafted concrete countertops, custom cabinetry, slate tile flooring, a large island and breakfast bar that will make entertaining easy.  Off the kitchen you'll find your large master where you will spend quiet nights in your industrial farmhouse en suite bathroom, soaking in your large jetted tub with beautiful panoramic views. When you head up one of your two specially designed staircases you will find plenty of space for kids or guests. Two bedrooms include jack and jill style bathroom but 2 separate private vanities and walk inn closets in each room. description: Recently sold: $225,000. WOW! Pride of ownership truly shines through on this move-in ready Cloquet split entry! This 2+ bedroom, 2 bath beauty is centrally located and within walking distance to schools, shopping, gas, movies, dining and churches. Updates include a Goodman gas F/A furnace 2017, central air 2017, Rheem 40 gal gas water heater, gas fireplace 2017, 30yr roof 2005. The main level offers a vaulted living room with gas fireplace, dining room and updated kitchen featuring vaulted ceiling, newer cabinets with dove-tailed drawers, linoleum flooring and dishwasher. The master bedroom is carpeted and has "his" and "hers" closets. In the main bath you will find a nicely tiled tub surround and ample linen storage. As you descend to the lower level, you will be pleasantly surprised by the amount of space in the over-sized rec room that is bright and cheery. The sauna will help rejuvenate you after a long day at the office and help take that chill out of your bones as "Old Man Winter" approaches. There is a non-legal bedroom (no egress window, but has a closet) that has been used as a pottery studio for decades. Rounding out the lower level is a huge storage room where you will find the laundry area and mechanicals. Located one block from the award-winning Washington Elementary School--one of seven MN Schools of Excellence statewide in 2019!  Let's add a 24x26 2 car attached garage, gutters & downspouts, C/A and a level, corner lot! This one will definitely impress from the moment you enter. BONUS....Seller is original owner/builder and NON SMOKER and NO pets!!!!  DO NOT HESITATE! Schedule your private showing today!

description: Recently sold: $192,400. Nestled in the woods on a dead end road you will find your own little get away on 1.15 acres. This home was built in 2014 on a heated slab. Handicap accessible, all electric home that is efficient to own. No city fees for water or sewer. Built to satisfy the buyer that would like their own private space Vs renting an apartment in town with room to expand in the future. Open floor plan, mini split AC and infloor heat, custom built kitchen with stainless and center island. The grounds feature a 24x30 detached garage, a couple sheds left over from the old homestead and a nice yard for your to finish however you choose. The location is GREAT with ski trails, hiking trails, biking and snowmobile trails right down the road. If your a pilot the private airport is a couple miles away. Its tucked behind an area of Cloquet that offers a quick trip right into town for shopping but you feel like your way out in the country. A must see.

description: Recently sold: $595,000. Custom built home and garage with 4,123 SF ($167 SF) of living space in a very private 1 acre setting. The property is located on a secluded bay with over 750' of shoreline on a dead end road. Positioned only 66' from the lake with a western exposure to enjoy the afternoon sun and exceptional sunsets. Douglas fir support beams from Washington State, handpicked fireplace bricks, and wall-lined windows provide a peaceful view of your private bay. High quality features throughout inc. a geo-thermo heating/air conditioning system. Pella windows, Hunter Douglas window treatments, Sub Zero refrigerator/freezer and wine refrigerator and Morning Star Wood Works cabinetry. The main house provides 2 bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, a large open L-Shaped living-dining-kitchen area and a private sitting/TV room. Wood burning fireplaces are located in the living room and an attached screened in veranda facing the lake. The 3-stall heated garage provides additional upstairs living space and sleeping area with a 3/4 bathroom. The heavily wooded grounds include lighted paths to a screened gazebo, several sitting areas and a hand laid brick fire circle with slate steps to the lake. There is also a separate sauna building with a wood burning stove and hand picked stones from the shores of Lake Superior. An Architecturally designed custom made dock system is specifically oriented for safe boat mooring, swimming and evening sunsets. Detailed records are available.

description: Recently sold: $175,000. Beautiful 100'x200' setting with this 3 bedroom, one level living. Recently sold: $45,000. Solid 1 bedroom, 1 bath home with a formal dining. Neat & clean ready to move in. Attached garage, large yard. Lots of updates.

Newer mechanicals, cedar siding, and all appliances can stay!

description: Recently sold: $236,800. First time on market, quality custom built, one owner home is being offered for the next owner to make it their own. Meticulously maintained, clean and move in ready. The driveway and sidewalk have life time pavers. Main level living w/ 3 BD's, full "pearl jetted tub" bath & a laundry room w/ built in desk, counters, storage closet w/ drop down ironboard and 1/2 bath. Mstr BD has large 8' glass sliding closet doors. Tiled kitchen is open to the dining room and has custom cabinetry w/ roll out drawers and a pantry with the same. Enjoy the enclosed screened porch right thru the sliding glass doors off the dining room. The large rec rm downstairs has a free standing wood FP, a pool table (which can stay) and an adjoining area for w/ a service counter and storage. Sauna for 4 or more, w/ a shower and sitting room. A large "bonus room", could be made into a 4th BD. Don't miss the workshop area, it has a 1/2 bath, cabinets, and power for anything. The 2 car garage has shelving & service doors in front and back. Home has lifetime seamless steel siding and gutters, which also have covers. Wonderful yard space with many perennials, including a grapevine covered gazebo and a storage shed. Also a fenced in  vegetable gardens. Close to schools, retail and freeway access. Make an appointment today, it may not be here tomorrow!

This home has room for everyone with 3 levels of living space, large living room with fireplace, formal dining room, grand foyer, sunroom, 2 offices, billiard room/music room. The kitchen has been completely redone & is a cook''s dream done by Lindquist & Company, which boasts an eat-in area, island, Wolf stove, double ovens, pantry, butler''s pantry & quartz countertops. description: Recently sold: $245,000. Looking for a property with space and privacy but not so much that you'll be spending all day maintaining it?  The search is over!!  3+ bed 2 bath home with all the comforts a homeowner could want and 6.44 acres... All 3 bedrooms are on the main floor along with laundry, no need for going up and down stairs, convenient layout for one level living! There is so much to appreciate at this home!  Maintenance free siding, newer windows, newer furnace, 2 car garage on a private setting just outside of Duluth. description: Recently sold: $355,000. Spacious 6 bedroom 3 bath home on 6.5 acres close to town.  Attached finished/heated garage plus a 28x56 garage that has a 28x28 2nd story  loft area, 220 amp electrical service, drive through with 3 garage doors. Home has over 3700+sq ft.  Nice big foyer entry.  Upper level features include:  Nice open floor plan,  big kitchen with center island and all new appliances. 2 dining areas.  Gas fireplace in living room.  Patio doors lead to deck overlooking the back yard.  Large bright sun room.    Master bedroom suite with walk in closet and bathroom with separate shower and whirlpool tub and private deck.   2 more bedrooms with large closets and 3/4 bath. Lower level offers walk out basement to nice patio area, 3 more bedrooms, full bathroom, rec room, and laundry room with counter top and sink. Lots of closets and storage area.  Compliant septic system. Property will be surveyed soon.

description:
Recently sold: $127,000. Available April 20, 2016 as the home is currently occupied. 

Move-in ready three bedroom, one and a half bath bungalow.  Built in 1924 and remodeled in 2009: Sheet rock, windows, plumbing, electrical, shingles, siding, insulation, kitchen cabinets and appliances. New water heater in 2012. High efficiency natural gas furnace, fresh paint and new carpet in 2015. Features include open living/dining area, spacious kitchen, 2 main floor bedrooms and a main floor full bath. Upstairs can be used in multiple ways; large master-suite with walk-in closet/dressing room or a bedroom with an extra sitting room and a half bath. The front porch catches your eye with a swing to enjoy too! Single car garage and generous yard with garden and fire pit. Quiet neighborhood close to schools, shopping, library, and more.

.

If you are interested in the house, please contact me via email or phone. Please be respectful and not approach the property with questions. Thank you for looking!!

.

This house qualifies for a USDA rural housing loan. (Section 502 direct loan program). 

.

Benefits include:
    - $0 down payment
    - Current low mortgage rate
    - Reduced mortgage insurance ( If 20% is not put down) 
    - Up to 33 year term
    - Low income qualification

description: Recently sold: $310,000. This exceptional upper-end quality home is just minutes from the Cloquet business district yet offers seclusion on a heavily wooded lot nestled among 100 year old white and red pines. The large fully windowed living room with massive stone gas fireplace shares a 240 degree panoramic view that enhances the beauty of the seasons. All one level with 36" wide solid oak doors and entries makes this home ideal for aging baby boomers and younger families alike. This beautiful home offers In-floor heat and 2 car garage and a second single garage gives added storage. The home is only 11 years old and is constructed with 2X6 walls and foam insulation. All appliances stay and it is full warranted for 1 year after purchase. The Septic is certified as compliant and the home is pre-wired for a generator. "WOW" best describes this home when visiting it for the first time. Don't miss it. Brokered And Advertised By: Edina Realty, Inc - Duluth Listing Agent: Lynn Bentfield

description: Recently sold: $250,000. Nestled on a dead-end street in the Historic part of old Cloquet sits this beautiful and stately grand Home in a park-like setting! Upstairs rooms have new windows as well as the kitchen, Formal dining room, front sitting room off the living room, Huge manicured yard with cute gardening shed with attached deck. Super private on almost an acre of land!

For sale: $299,900. For Sale Completely remodeled modular country home on 5 acres that is also a rental property or mother in law apartment! The main level has 3 remodeled bedrooms and two full baths. New hickory kitchen, all new appliances, new kitchen flooring, new sliding glass door and entry doors. Main level laundry room with kitchenette and laundry storage. Vaulted ceilings throughout living room and kitchen. New water softener, new air exchanger, new water heater, new furnace. There are 2 new decks with 6 x 6 post construction. Huge brand new double-width garage that is a full 42 feet long with two 16' doors plus a side overhead door for UTV or tractor entry.
Downstairs all construction is new and only 6 months old. Two egress windows and new entry door. Vinyl plank flooring, new white shaker kitchen, all new appliances. New washer/dryer stackable unit, new full bath with ceramic tile flooring. Walk in closet. Plus it is already rented with a long-term tenant and if you owner occupy, it will drop your monthly payment by 800 per month.
Huge yard with no visible neighbors in any direction. Enjoy sunsets on the new deck overlooking the canopy of trees with deer in the backyard. It is rural, yet only 8 minutes north of Cloquet and only 1 block off blacktop. The upper main level would rent for 1800 as each unit would have a full two stalls in garage. Owner currently owner occupies. The rent it brings in drops your payment in half!! Listing for 299,900. (Note that overhead google views are not accurate for some reason) Downstairs apartment could also be used as a mother in law apartment as it is fully functioning yet accessible both from main level as well as ground level access from the outside
218-590-7492

description: Recently sold: $185,000. Newly remodeled 4 bedrooms, 2 ½ bath home located in Cloquet, conveniently located near the Cloquet schools and parks. There are beautiful oak hardwood floors throughout the entryway, living room, dining room, hallway and main floor bedroom. The upstairs is complete with 2 bedrooms and a half bath and downstairs has a large family room, laundry room, and a spacious master suite with a walk-through closet and private full bathroom. There is also plenty of storage in the basement utility room, with the potential of a cellar.
